LakeSense's replication-engine architecture was informed by studying
open-source projects including OLake (Apache 2.0,
https://github.com/datazip-inc/olake). LakeSense is a clean reimplementation:
no OLake source code is copied or derived. Benchmark numbers, where published,
are LakeSense's own measurements — never OLake's.

Open-core model: everything in this repository is free and open under Apache
2.0, including the features other vendors reserve for paid tiers (data-diff
validation, escalation/on-call, audit logs, cost analytics, lineage, quality
monitors, config versioning, environments, backfills). SSO/RBAC and compliance
packs are reserved for a future LakeSense Pro tier.
